      • getDateType

        public static facebook.FacebookBirthDateUtil.DateType getDateType(java.lang.String date)
        Figures out the date type of a facebook date. Note that this function makes no checks whether the date itself is valid. A date using the 13th month, as 13/01/2001 will as such still be considered a FULL type.
        Parameters:
        date - A date formatted as one of the types specified by DateType
        Returns:
        The deduced DateType of the input string. INVALID is returned if no type matched.
        See Also:
        FacebookBirthDateUtil.DateType

      • formatDate

        public static facebook.FacebookBirthDateUtil.FacebookBirthDate formatDate(java.lang.String date)
        Converts a string date to a LocalDate object. As NULL is valid for parts of a date, missing parts will default to day 1, month 1, year 0. The type of the date should always be checked before using the date contents.
        Parameters:
        date - A date string, as Å•eturned by the Facebook API
        Returns:
        Object consisting of the type of date, as well as a LocalDate
